  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6766 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma concentration (6760-6770 strikes all showing -15B+ GEX), dealers are being forced to buy this breakout move and will continue buying any further upside until we clear 6780 where positive gamma kicks in. The regime is clearly BREAKOUT with dealers short gamma, meaning they're amplifying moves rather than providing stabilization - expect volatile trending behavior with momentum feeding on itself. Key inflection at 6780 (+9.7B positive gamma wall) where dealer flow flips from buying rallies to selling them, making it critical resistance.\n\n**Bottom line:** dealers must keep buying this rally until 6780, expect volatile upside momentum.",
